@startuml
actor Student
participant Browser
participant "AuthController" as Controller
participant "CookieCsrfTokenRepository" as CsrfRepo
participant "AuthService" as Auth
participant "AuthenticationManager" as AuthManager
participant "DaoAuthenticationProvider" as AuthProvider
participant "CustomUserDetailsService" as UserDetails
participant "MfaService" as MFA
participant "JwtAuthenticationFilter" as JwtFilter
participant "JwtService" as Jwt
participant "AuthCookieService" as Cookie
database DB

Browser -> Controller : GET /api/auth/csrf over HTTPS
Controller -> CsrfRepo : generateToken(request)
CsrfRepo --> Controller : CSRF token
Controller -> CsrfRepo : saveToken(token, request, response)
CsrfRepo --> Browser : readable XSRF-TOKEN cookie
note over Browser,Controller
Frontend boots CSRF before unsafe requests and sends
X-XSRF-TOKEN plus credentialed cookies on POST requests.
end note

Student -> Browser : enter name, email, password
Browser -> Controller : POST /api/auth/register + X-XSRF-TOKEN
Controller -> Auth : register(request)
Auth -> DB : check unique email + load STUDENT role
Auth -> DB : store user with BCrypt password hash
Auth -> Jwt : generateToken(amr=[pwd], mfa=false)
Jwt --> Auth : signed JWT
Auth --> Controller : AuthResponse(..., token present internally)
Controller -> Cookie : createAuthenticationCookie(jwt)
Cookie --> Controller : Set-Cookie header
Controller --> Browser : 201 Created + HttpOnly auth cookie + token omitted from body

Student -> Browser : later enters email + password
Browser -> Controller : POST /api/auth/login + X-XSRF-TOKEN
Controller -> Auth : login(credentials)
Auth -> AuthManager : authenticate(email, password)
AuthManager -> AuthProvider : authenticate(...)
AuthProvider -> UserDetails : loadUserByUsername(email)
UserDetails -> DB : load user by email
DB --> UserDetails : user with bcrypt password hash + roles
AuthProvider -> AuthProvider : verify with BCryptPasswordEncoder
AuthProvider --> AuthManager : authenticated principal
AuthManager --> Auth : authentication success
Auth -> DB : load normalized user record
DB --> Auth : user + MFA state

alt MFA disabled for this account
  Auth -> Jwt : generateToken(amr=[pwd], mfa=false)
  Jwt --> Auth : signed JWT
  Auth --> Controller : AuthResponse(authStatus=AUTHENTICATED, token)
  Controller -> Cookie : createAuthenticationCookie(jwt)
  Cookie --> Controller : Set-Cookie header
  Controller --> Browser : 200 OK + HttpOnly auth cookie
else MFA enabled for this account
  Auth -> MFA : createLoginChallenge(user)
  MFA -> DB : delete expired/prior challenges
  MFA -> DB : store short-lived MFA challenge
  DB --> MFA : challengeId + expiry + attempts
  MFA --> Auth : AuthResponse(authStatus=MFA_REQUIRED, no token)
  Auth --> Controller : MFA challenge metadata
  Controller -> Cookie : clearAuthenticationCookie()
  Cookie --> Controller : clearing Set-Cookie header
  Controller --> Browser : 200 OK + MFA challenge metadata

  Student -> Browser : enter authenticator or recovery code
  Browser -> Controller : POST /api/auth/mfa/verify + X-XSRF-TOKEN
  Controller -> MFA : verify(challengeId, verificationCode)
  MFA -> DB : load challenge + user MFA secret/recovery data
  DB --> MFA : pending challenge + protected MFA state
  MFA -> MFA : validate TOTP or consume recovery code
  MFA -> DB : mark challenge consumed / recovery code used
  MFA -> Jwt : generateToken(amr=[pwd, otp], mfa=true)
  Jwt --> MFA : signed JWT
  MFA --> Controller : AuthResponse(authStatus=AUTHENTICATED, token)
  Controller -> Cookie : createAuthenticationCookie(jwt)
  Cookie --> Controller : Set-Cookie header
  Controller --> Browser : 200 OK + HttpOnly auth cookie
end

Browser -> JwtFilter : GET /api/auth/me with credentialed auth cookie
JwtFilter -> Cookie : extractToken(request cookies)
alt auth cookie present
  Cookie --> JwtFilter : JWT from auth cookie
else no auth cookie
  JwtFilter -> JwtFilter : fallback to Authorization: Bearer header
end
JwtFilter -> Jwt : extract username and validate token
Jwt --> JwtFilter : valid subject + claims
JwtFilter -> UserDetails : loadUserByUsername(subject)
UserDetails -> DB : load user by email
DB --> UserDetails : user details + roles
JwtFilter --> Controller : authenticated SecurityContext
Controller -> Auth : currentUser(authentication.name)
Auth -> DB : load current user
DB --> Auth : user profile + roles
Auth --> Controller : CurrentUserResponse
Controller --> Browser : 200 OK + CurrentUserResponse

note right of AuthProvider
Plaintext passwords are not stored.
Spring Security verifies only the bcrypt password hash.
end note

note right of MFA
No authenticated session cookie is established
before second-factor success.
TOTP secrets are AES-GCM protected at rest and
recovery codes are one-time backup credentials.
end note

note right of Jwt
JWT supports stateless session validation,
but it is not a data-encryption mechanism.
Invalid JWTs are ignored by the filter and fail later
at authorization boundaries.
end note

note over Browser,Controller
The browser-facing contract is cookie-first:
- JWT is transported in an HttpOnly auth cookie
- frontend sends credentialed requests and bootstraps CSRF automatically
- response bodies omit the raw token value
- validation, malformed-body, ResponseStatusException, and AuthApiException
  failures use a shared structured envelope
- some Spring Security / CSRF / authorization failures remain plain 401/403 responses
end note
@enduml

